cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.DL, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the optimization of data access methods in XML databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The use of path summaries and path partitioning also relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the practical algorithms and experiments involve deep learning (cs.DL) and cryptography (cs.CR).
